<subSubSection id="3CAE8C8BEE0C35A05459D4B7AF4BEFC8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="C864D8B4AA6590739A77EB374AE2264D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A54FC341FF48AF32DC7D1E22C17EA1C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="83C11EBA06FE7AD27FDC7C18DC279F0D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="637BF5FE7E3E6CF16217FE90C94483BF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Morphology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The largest species occurring in the Caucasus. The body size of larvae 20-24 mm, cerci 20-22 mm (
<bibRefCitation id="070F29F73D626ADE20E64D0658869426" author="Braasch, D" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Nachrichten" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="65 - 70" refId="B6" refString="Braasch, D, 1978. Epeorus znojkoi and Iron magnus new species (Heptageniidae Ephemeroptera) from the Caucasus USSR. Entomologische Nachrichten 22: 65 - 70" title="Epeorus znojkoi and Iron magnus new species (Heptageniidae Ephemeroptera) from the Caucasus USSR." volume="22" year="1978">Braasch 1978</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="807C85419FF749352E9E47384ACF3764" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="07B3FBA1FD5033ED886D939051580376" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="978623BDF45812BE1C154D74C4EBDA92" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Taxonomy</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Original description based on the larvae from Russia (western Caucasus) (
<bibRefCitation id="95CE7C908C682D25D964BC1C110C8757" author="Braasch, D" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Nachrichten" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="65 - 70" refId="B6" refString="Braasch, D, 1978. Epeorus znojkoi and Iron magnus new species (Heptageniidae Ephemeroptera) from the Caucasus USSR. Entomologische Nachrichten 22: 65 - 70" title="Epeorus znojkoi and Iron magnus new species (Heptageniidae Ephemeroptera) from the Caucasus USSR." volume="22" year="1978">Braasch 1978</bibRefCitation>
). The type series is currently deposited in the collection of Stuttgart State Museum of Natural History, Stuttgart, Germany (SMNS). Imagines (male and female) and female subimago described by 
<bibRefCitation id="AEDABA284E882AAFC6931E568A9FC625" author="Braasch, D" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Nachrichten" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="166 - 173" refId="B8" refString="Braasch, D, 1980. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Gattung Iron Eaton (Heptageniidae, Ephemeroptera) im Kaukasus (UdSSR), 2. Entomologische Nachrichten 24: 166 - 173" title="Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Gattung Iron Eaton (Heptageniidae, Ephemeroptera) im Kaukasus (UdSSR), 2." volume="24" year="1980">Braasch (1980)</bibRefCitation>
based on material from Russia, Armenia and Georgia. We assume the larva of 
<taxonomicName id="3C8060A8C4BBA9A1630216B617B35B2F" genus="E." lsidName="E. (C.) magnus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="magnus" subGenus="C.">E. (C.) magnus</taxonomicName>
was erroneously described under the name 
<taxonomicName id="8D6F1B545DEC0195C5E63A754D450E5A" genus="E." lsidName="znojkoi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="znojkoi">
<emphasis id="79394CD304B976852D1947611F35E6BD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">znojkoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="C061F9481E55EAC8A15A5344AC3067E5" author="Sinitshenkova, ND" journalOrPublisher="Entomological Review" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="85 - 92" refId="B43" refString="Sinitshenkova, ND, 1976. Mayflies of the genus Iron Eaton (Ephemeroptera, Heptageniidae) in the fauna of the Caucasus. Entomological Review 55: 85 - 92" title="Mayflies of the genus Iron Eaton (Ephemeroptera, Heptageniidae) in the fauna of the Caucasus." volume="55" year="1976">Sinitshenkova (1976)</bibRefCitation>
(see remarks to 
<taxonomicName id="E8AE8EB343DD795A34F2A347883AAFD2" genus="E." lsidName="E. (C.) znojkoi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="znojkoi" subGenus="C.">E. (C.) znojkoi</taxonomicName>
s. l. for details).
</paragraph>
